# Tailwind CSS & UI Guidelines

## Tailwind CSS 4 Syntax

### Theme Configuration

```css
/* src/assets/styles/tailwind.css */
@import "tailwindcss";

@theme {
  /* Custom animations */
  --animate-fade-in: fade-in 0.2s ease-out;
  --animate-slide-up: slide-up 0.3s ease-out;
  --animate-spin-slow: spin 20s linear infinite;
  
  /* Custom colors for analytics events */
  --color-event-track: #3b82f6;    /* Blue */
  --color-event-page: #10b981;     /* Green */
  --color-event-identify: #8b5cf6; /* Purple */
  --color-event-group: #f59e0b;    /* Amber */
  --color-event-error: #ef4444;    /* Red */
  
  @keyframes fade-in {
    from { opacity: 0; }
    to { opacity: 1; }
  }
  
  @keyframes slide-up {
    from { 
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(10px);
    }
    to { 
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }
}
```

## Dark Theme for DevTools

DevTools panels should use dark theme to match browser DevTools:

```tsx
// ✅ Use dark backgrounds with light text
<div className="bg-gray-900 text-gray-100">
  <header className="bg-gray-800 border-b border-gray-700">
    <h1 className="text-white font-semibold">Segment Events</h1>
  </header>
</div>

// ✅ Event type color coding
<span className={`px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-medium ${
  event.type === 'track' ? 'bg-blue-500/20 text-blue-400' :
  event.type === 'page' ? 'bg-green-500/20 text-green-400' :
  event.type === 'identify' ? 'bg-purple-500/20 text-purple-400' :
  'bg-gray-500/20 text-gray-400'
}`}>
  {event.type}
</span>
```

## Component Styling Patterns

### Utility-First Approach

```tsx
// ✅ Use Tailwind utility classes
<div className="flex flex-col gap-2 p-4 bg-gray-900 border border-gray-700">
  <span className="text-sm font-medium text-gray-200">{event.name}</span>
  <span className="text-xs text-gray-400">{formatTime(event.timestamp)}</span>
</div>

// ❌ Avoid inline styles
<div style={{ display: 'flex', padding: '16px' }}>
```

### Conditional Classes

```tsx
// ✅ Template literals for simple conditions
<div className={`p-4 ${isSelected ? 'bg-blue-900' : 'bg-gray-800'}`}>

// ✅ Use clsx/cn for complex conditions
import { cn } from '@src/lib/utils';

<div className={cn(
  "p-4 transition-colors",
  isSelected && "bg-blue-900 ring-1 ring-blue-500",
  isHovered && "bg-gray-700",
  isDisabled && "opacity-50 cursor-not-allowed"
)}>
```

### Responsive Design

```tsx
// ✅ Mobile-first responsive classes
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">

// Extension popups have fixed dimensions
<div className="w-[400px] h-[500px] overflow-hidden">
```

